twitch-tag-mp3 (0.4.0) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Add --json/-J flag to emit all log output as newline-delimited JSON.
  * Skip writing ID3 tags when all fields are already up to date.
  * Log each changed tag field with old and new value before rewriting.
  * Preserve original GID of MP3 files after writing tags; die if GID
    cannot be restored.
  * Add artist name mappings: HANAWINS, FaBiESto, A_D_A_M_S_K_I, Fraser
    Binnie, XiJaro & Pitch, Bugi, Ferry Corsten, Noemi Black, Stoneface &
    Terminal, DJ DNA.
  * Lowercase conjunctions (on/and/or) in middle words of artist names.
  * Split trailing 'world' into a separate word in artist names.
  * Fix camelCase splitting to avoid incorrectly splitting NViolent.
  * Include COMM tag in unchanged-tags check and change logging.
  * Strip ()[lang]: prefix from COMM frame when reading via id3v2 -l.
  * Remove $URL from COMM tag value.
  * Add missing libipc-run3-perl Debian dependency.

 -- Rev. Duncan Ross Palmer <2e0eol@gmail.com>  Fri, 14 Mar 2026 18:50:00 +0000

twitch-tag-mp3 (0.3.0) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Add --directory/-d and --jobs/-j command-line flags.
  * Add --verbose/-v flag
  * Completely new track and astist tag generation logic
  * we now use the id3v2 as a helper due to a temporary-file handling bug in MP3::Tag
  * Update packaging for Debian Trixie: debhelper-compat 13, Standards-Version 4.7.3.
  * Add Rules-Requires-Root: no.
  * Remove deprecated debian/compat file.
  * Fix duplicate copyright line and typo in debian/copyright.

 -- Rev. Duncan Ross Palmer <2e0eol@gmail.com>  Tue, 10 Mar 2026 08:06:24 +0000

